      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STEELY ZAC (6) made a good start to his career when he came from the back row to be beaten 2 metres into third at this circuit and distance. Open to natural improvement so has winning claims. LUCIENDO BIEN (11) started favourite on debut but broke after the start and finished fourth at Newcastle. Gets a tough barrier as a result but had been trialling well prior so looks to have ability and will be better for the experience. LOCHINVAR COOGEE (2) will be fitter and draws much better so deserves consideration after finishing midfield when resuming at Newcastle. MIRACLE SLOY (1) has been solid at the trials and the ace draw could see him kick off his career with a win.",
